Package: imputefinder
Title: Classify Missing Values in Quantitative Proteomics Data
Version: 0.99.0
Authors@R:
    person("Emir", "Turkes", , "emir.turkes@eturkes.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-2345-6789"))
Description: Provides a flexible method for distinguishing between Missing
    Not At Random (MNAR) and Missing At Random (MAR) values in
    quantitative proteomics data such as label-free quantification (LFQ).
    The package uses intensity distributions and elbow detection on the
    cumulative missingness curve to classify features per experimental
    condition and returns a filtered SummarizedExperiment together with
    classified feature sets and per-condition cutoffs.
